# PHASES: slint-gui-mcp

## Phase 1 / scaffold (done)
- 6-layer hexagonal MVVM topology (ui / adapter / core / pal / shared / state)
- 7 original MCP tools: screenshot_window, find_element, click_element, type_text, send_keys, get_window_info, list_windows
- Core NCC template matcher (vision_core)
- Win32 PAL: HWND find, GDI capture, PostMessage input
- Smoke tests for tool registration and live-window flows

## Phase 2 / stabilization (done)
- +5 MCP tools: select_all, copy, cut, paste, screenshot_burst
- Encoding cleanup (UTF-8 comments and docs)
- Background capture via PrintWindow + SendMessage (no foreground steal)
- Negative-path tests for error payloads
- Split GUI notepad tests into dedicated test file

## Phase 3 / precision (current)
- +2 MCP tools: click_at, crop_region
- click_at: click at absolute client coordinates without template matching
- crop_region: crop a rectangle from a window screenshot and return as base64 PNG
- Template library support: AI can capture regions and reuse them as templates

## Phase 4 / robustness (planned)
- HWND-id targeting: bypass title matching for known windows
- DPI-aware coordinates: scale coords for high-DPI and mixed-DPI setups
- WM_GETTEXT / WM_SETTEXT: read and write edit control text directly
- GPU fallback: alternative capture path for GPU-accelerated windows
